Cache middleware that uses Cache API: <https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Cache>

Minimal implementation is here:

```ts
app.get('*', async (c, next) => {
  const key = c.req.url
  const cache = caches.default
  const response = await cache.match(key)
  if (!response) {
    await next()
    c.executionCtx.waitUntil(cache.put(key, c.res.clone()))
  } else {
    return response
  }
})
```

It will be "built-in middleware" because it's only using Web Standard API.

Cache API is supported only on Cloudflare Workers deployed on the custom domain. But, Deno will support in the future: <https://deno.com/deploy/docs/runtime-api>

