This is efficient, but it is not welcome to extend the Web Standard's Request object. Because it's "standard". So I think it's good to make `HonoReuqest` for wrapping `Request` object.

```ts
class HonoRequest {
  request: Request
  constructor(request: Request) {
    this.request = request
  }

  header(key: string) {
    return this.request.headers.get(key)
  }
  
  //...
}
```

