These are utilities for helping to make a schema for the validator and enabling to create the types from the schema.

Using `buildSchema`, we can make the schema that defines what we want to get from the request:

```ts
const schema = buildSchema((v) => ({
  id: v.json('post.id'),
  title: v.json('post.title'),
  author: v.object('post.author', (v) => ({
    name: v.json('name'),
    age: v.json('age').asNumber(),
  })),
}))
```

We can pass it to the validator middleware:

```ts
app.post('/post', validator(schema), (c) => {
  const post = c.req.valid()
  createPost(post)
  return c.json({
    message: 'success!',
  })
})
```

`Infer` is "type" to get the type from schema:

```ts
type Post = Infer<typeof schema>
```

`Post` will be:

```ts
type Post = {
  id: string
  title: string
  author: {
    name: string
    age: number
  }
}
```

Then, you can use `Post` for the models and logics:

```ts
const posts: Post[] = []

const getPosts = (): Post[] => posts
const createPost = (arg: Post) => {
  posts.push(arg)
}
```

