There are two problems:

## 1. Root path not matches

```typescript
// Matches `http://www1.example.com/hello`
app.get('www1.example.com/hello', (c) => c.text('hello www1'))

// Not matches `http://www1.example.com/`
app.get('www1.example.com', (c) => c.text('hello www1 root'))
```

To deal with this, `getPath` should remove the trailing slash from the path.
(Or add trailing slash to the pattern like `app.get('www1.example.com/', ...)`; it's not very instinctive)

## 2. Grouping route does not matches
For some unknown reason, grouping is not works when path pattern have no preceding slash.
```typescript
sub.get('/', ...)

// Not matches `http://www1.example.com/sub`
app.route('www1.example.com/sub', sub)
```

To deal with this, `getPath` should add preceding slash to path. And path patterns should start with a `/`.

## Solution

Use `getPath: (req) => req.url.replace(/^https?:\//, '').replace(/(.)\/$/, '$1')` with slash-preceded patterns .

