Hello!
First off, thank you for creating Hono. I'm using it in my personal projects and it's been a great experience!

This pull request aims to improve type inference when extending context variables in middlewares.

Currently, When using handlers like `app.get` to register middlewares that extends context variables, the context type is correctly inferred.

```typescript
const app = new Hono()
const mw = createMiddleware<{ Variables: { foo: string } }>(async () => {});

app.get(mw, async (c) => {
    // this is correctly typed.
    const foo: string = c.var.foo
})
```

However, when using `app.use`, the types aren't as well defined.

```typescript
app.use(mw).get(async (c) => {
    // this isn't correctly typed before merging this PR.
    const foo: string = c.var.foo
})
```

While `app.use` can accept path parametrers like `app.use('/foo', ...)`, but the type inference in these cases is quite complex and isn't covered in this PR.

I believe this improvement will make Hono even more robust for TypeScript users. Looking forward to your feedback!

