Fixes #2034, #2035

### Update `startViewTransition()` family

Forgot to mention in the previous PR that `document.startViewTransition()` is currently only available in Google Chrome and Edge.
https://caniuse.com/mdn-api_document_startviewtransition

This PR adds the following new items
```ts
import { useViewTransition } from 'hono/jsx'
import { viewTransition } from 'hono/css'
// or dom-specific version import { viewTransition } from 'hono/jsx/dom/css'
```

In the following, we will look at the usage of the `startViewTransition()` family along with these usages.

#### Easiest example

Simply call `startViewTransition()` function (not a hook).

```tsx
import { startViewTransition } from 'hono/jsx'

const Content = () => {
  const [showLargeImage, setShowLargeImage] = useState(false)
  return (
    <>
      <button onClick={() => startViewTransition(() => setShowLargeImage((state) => !state))}>
        Click!
      </button>
      <div>
        {!showLargeImage ? (
          <img src='https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/98495527' />
        ) : (
          <div
            class={css`
              background: url('https://github.com/honojs/hono/blob/main/docs/images/hono-logo.png?raw=true');
              background-size: contain;
              background-repeat: no-repeat;
              background-position: center;
              width: 600px;
              height: 600px;
            `}
          ></div>
        )}
      </div>
    </>
  )
}
```

#### Next Step

You can use `viewTransition()` helper for getting unique `view-transition-name`.

```tsx
import { startViewTransition } from 'hono/jsx'

const Content = () => {
  const [showLargeImage, setShowLargeImage] = useState(false)
  const [transitionNameClass] = useState(() => viewTransition())
  return (
    <>
      <button onClick={() => startViewTransition(() => setShowLargeImage((state) => !state))}>
        Click!
      </button>
      <div>
        {!showLargeImage ? (
          <img src='https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/98495527' class={transitionNameClass} />
        ) : (
          <div
            class={css`
              ${transitionNameClass}
              background: url('https://github.com/honojs/hono/blob/main/docs/images/hono-logo.png?raw=true');
              background-size: contain;
              background-repeat: no-repeat;
              background-position: center;
              width: 600px;
              height: 600px;
            `}
          ></div>
        )}
      </div>
    </>
  )
}
```

#### Use with `keyframes`

`::view-transition-old()` is converted to `::view-transition-old(${uniqueName)`

```tsx
import { startViewTransition } from 'hono/jsx'

const rotate = keyframes`
  from {
    rotate: 0deg;
  }
  to {
    rotate: 360deg;
  }
`

const Content = () => {
  const [showLargeImage, setShowLargeImage] = useState(false)
  const [transitionNameClass] = useState(() =>
    viewTransition(css`
      ::view-transition-old() {
        animation-name: ${rotate};
      }
      ::view-transition-new() {
        animation-name: ${rotate};
      }
    `)
  )
  return (
    <>
      <button onClick={() => startViewTransition(() => setShowLargeImage((state) => !state))}>
        Click!
      </button>
      <div>
        {!showLargeImage ? (
          <img src='https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/98495527' class={transitionNameClass} />
        ) : (
          <div
            class={css`
              ${transitionNameClass}
              background: url('https://github.com/honojs/hono/blob/main/docs/images/hono-logo.png?raw=true');
              background-size: contain;
              background-repeat: no-repeat;
              background-position: center;
              width: 600px;
              height: 600px;
            `}
          ></div>
        )}
      </div>
    </>
  )
}
```

#### If you want to change the style only during the animation

You can use `useViewTransition()`.  This hook returns `[boolean, (callback: () => void) => void]` and they are `isUpdating` flag and `startViewTransition()` function.
If you want to change the style only during the animation, you can specify the style if `isUpdating` is `true`.

When this hook is used, Component is evaluated at the following two times.
* Inside the callback of a call to `startViewTransition()`.
* When the `finish` promise becomes fulfilled
    * https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/ViewTransition/finished


```tsx
import { useViewTransition } from 'hono/jsx'

const rotate = keyframes`
  from {
    rotate: 0deg;
  }
  to {
    rotate: 360deg;
  }
`

const Content = () => {
  const [isUpdating, startViewTransition] = useViewTransition()
  const [showLargeImage, setShowLargeImage] = useState(false)
  const [transitionNameClass] = useState(() =>
    viewTransition(css`
      ::view-transition-old() {
        animation: ${rotate} 2s ease-in-out;
      }
      ::view-transition-new() {
        animation: ${rotate} 2s ease-in-out;
      }
    `)
  )
  return (
    <>
      <button onClick={() => startViewTransition(() => setShowLargeImage((state) => !state))}>
        Click!
      </button>
      <div>
        {!showLargeImage ? (
          <img src='https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/98495527' class={transitionNameClass} />
        ) : (
          <div
            class={css`
              ${transitionNameClass}
              background: url('https://github.com/honojs/hono/blob/main/docs/images/hono-logo.png?raw=true');
              background-size: contain;
              background-repeat: no-repeat;
              background-position: center;
              width: 600px;
              height: 600px;
              position: relative;
              ${isUpdating &&
              css`
                &:before {
                  content: 'Loading...';
                  position: absolute;
                  top: 50%;
                  left: 50%;
                }
              `}
            `}
          ></div>
        )}
      </div>
    </>
  )
}
```


