But the latest version of Workers Types (`4.20240312.0`) now includes an `abort` method, so it looks like this:
```ts
declare interface ExecutionContext {
  waitUntil(promise: Promise<any>): void;
  passThroughOnException(): void;
  abort(reason?: any): void;
}
```

Reference: https://github.com/Cloudflare-Mining/Cloudflare-Datamining/blob/f3eb65cf6548395775b58955b5c0d4543b9e2d2a/data/workers-types/experimental/index.ts#L313

So if you have a function that expects a context like:

```ts
function fooBar(ctx: ExecutionContext) {
	///stuff
}
```

